  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">ColumnWidth</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For MODFLOW and PHAST models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ColumnWidth</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">({Column}) returns the width of the cell or element column specified by its one optional argument Column.  If the optional argument is not included, the function uses the column of the node or element for which the formula is being calculated. For SUTRA models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">ColumnWidth</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns zero.</text></para>
  </body>
